d</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Baroness Maud of Buckland was born about 1225, in Folkestone, Kent, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Hamo De Crevequer."},"et":{"about 1225–":"umbes 1225–Surnud","1224–1263":"1224–1263","1245–1301":"1245–1301","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1225":"1225","Abt 1245":"umbes 1245","1301":"1301","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","about 1225":"umbes 1225","1263":"1263","Folkestone, Kent, England":"Folkestone, Kent, England","Folkestone,Kent,England.":"Folkestone, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1225–":"noin 1225–Kuollut","1224–1263":"1224–1263","1245–1301":"1245–1301","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1225":"1225","Abt 1245":"noin 1245","1301":"1301","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","about 1225":"noin 1225","1263":"1263","Folkestone, Kent, England":"Folkestone, Kent, England","Folkestone,Kent,England.":"Folkestone, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1225–":"environ 1225–Décédée","1224–1263":"1224–1263","1245–1301":"1245–1301","1225–Female":"1225–Décédée","1225":"1225","Abt 1245":"environ 1245","1301":"1301","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","about 1225":"environ 1225","1263":"1263","Folkestone, Kent, England":"Folkestone, Kent, Angleterre","Folkestone,Kent,England.":"Folkestone, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Baroness Maud of Buckland est née environ 1225, à Folkestone, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Hamo De Crevequer."},"de":{"about 1225–":"um 1225–Verstorben","1224–1263":"1224–1263","1245–1301":"1245–130